Whitelisted products:
- Claude Code (https://claude.ai/code)
- Cursor (https://cursor.sh)
- GitHub Copilot (https://github.com/features/copilot)
- Windsurf (https://codeium.com/windsurf)
- Devin (https://devin.ai)
- Aider (https://aider.chat)
- Continue (https://continue.dev)
- Codex CLI (https://developers.openai.com/codex/changelog/)
- Gemini CLI (https://geminicli.com/docs/changelogs/)

Research tasks (for each product):
1) Check official site/blog/changelog/release notes
2) Check GitHub releases (if exists)
3) Scan recent news/discussions (HN/Reddit/X/blogs)
4) Identify version releases, new features, major updates
5) Collect community/user feedback or requests about the update (quotes/snippets with source)
   - Prioritize credible, recent, high-signal threads (HN, Reddit, X, official forums)
   - Look for: user requests, pain points, praise, complaints, adoption signals
   - Capture short quotes/snippets with source links; avoid long copy/paste
   - If sentiment is unclear, default to `neutral`

Output format (JSON array):
```json
[
  {
    "productName": "Exact name from whitelist above",
    "title": "Update headline or feature name",
    "description": "What changed, was announced, or released (1–3 sentences)",
    "updateType": "feature | bugfix | announcement | release",
    "url": "https://link-to-announcement-or-release-notes",
    "date": "YYYY-MM-DD",
    "community_feedback": [
      {
        "quote": "Short user/community reaction or request",
        "source": "HN | Reddit | X | Forum | Blog comments",
        "sentiment": "positive | neutral | negative"
      }
    ]
  }
]
```
- If no valid updates in the 7–14 day window, return `[]`.

File output + incremental updates:
- Maintain `whitelist-updates.json` in the current working directory.
- After every step (including each “Record progress, rewrite todo”), overwrite `whitelist-updates.json` with the best current JSON (start with `[]` if nothing yet).
- Final state must hold the sorted array of updates.

