      "Based on the search results, I found information about Claude Code updates and new features in 2026. Here's what I discovered:\n\n## Claude Code 2.1.0/2.1.1 - January 2026 Update\n\nThe search results reveal that **Claude Code 2.1.0** (with a quick hotfix to 2.1.1) was released in early January 2026 as the first major version update of the year. Here are the key new features:\n\n### Major Features Added:\n\n1. **Skills Hot Reload** - Skills created or modified in `~/.claude/skills` or `.claude/skills` can now be used immediately without restarting the session\n\n2. **Language Configuration** - New language settings to configure Claude's response language (e.g., `language: \"japanese\"`)\n\n3. **Enhanced Skills Capabilities**:\n   - Skill branch execution using `context: fork` to run skills and slash commands in independent sub-agent contexts\n   - Agent type specification in skills using the `agent` field\n   - Hook support in frontmatter (PreToolUse, PostToolUse, and Stop hooks)\n\n4. **Git Integration Improvements**:\n   - New `respectGitignore` support in settings.json for @ mention file selector behavior\n   - Remote session commands (`/teleport` and `/remote-env`) for claude.ai subscribers\n\n5. **UI/UX Enhancements**:\n   - Improved shortcut key support (Shift+Enter now works out-of-the-box in iTerm2, WezTerm, Ghostty, and Kitty)\n   - New `IS_DEMO` environment variable to hide email and organization info for recordings\n   - Enhanced Vim motions with new operations and text objects\n\n6. **Access Control**:\n   - Ability to disable specific agents using `Task(AgentName)` syntax in settings.json permissions or `--disallowedTools` CLI flag\n\n7. **Usage Tracking** - `/usage` command to track usage (from version 2.0.0)\n\n### Installation/Upgrade:\nUsers can upgrade via:\n- `npm update -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code`\n- `npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code@2.1.1`\n- Check version with: `claude --version`\n\nFor the complete and official changelog, you can check the [GitHub repository](https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code)."
