3314/374279789?_ugc_source=ugcbaiducard\"},{\"title\":\"Anthropic（美国人工智能股份有限公司）\",\"url\":\"https://baike.baidu.com/item/Anthropic/62639515\"},{\"title\":\"ClaudeCode引爆2026！从2045到2026，技术奇点真的来了？\",\"url\":\"https://m.163.com/dy/article/KILK5B23055616X8.html\"},{\"title\":\"2026年该如何使用Claude Code？！\",\"url\":\"https://view.inews.qq.com/wxn/20260104A02TQA00?openid=o04IBAG6-XivUDEmy3eNIu7sPqgY&reJumped=1&strategy=&tbkt=I&uid=\"},{\"title\":\"AI系统提示词：Claude 4 Opus\",\"url\":\"https://m.blog.csdn.net/weixin_39415598/article/details/148431289\"},{\"title\":\"Anthropic公司新推出的Claude模型能够提供即时反应与深思熟虑的回答\",\"url\":\"https://baijiahao.baidu.com/s?id=1824995381134762767\"},{\"title\":\"告别Ctrl+C/V！AI智能体正式接管你的工作流\",\"url\":\"https://www.xianjichina.com/special/detail_594258.html\"},{\"title\":\"Claude 5 最新消息汇总：2026 年Anthropic 下一代AI 模型6 大亮点解析\",\"url\":\"https://help.apiyi.com/claude-5-latest-news-2026-features-release.html\"}]\n\nBased on my search results, I found several articles mentioning Claude Code updates in **January and February 2026**, but **none of these results are from official Anthropic or claude.ai sources**. Here's what I found from third-party sources:\n\n---\n\n## **Claude Code Updates - February 2026 (Third-Party Reports)**\n\n### **New Model Releases (February 2026)**\n\n**Claude Opus 4.6** (Released February 5, 2026)\n- **100K token context window** (beta version testing up to **1 million tokens** - capable of processing ~750 books)\n- **Agent Teams multi-agent collaboration**: Multiple AI agents working in parallel, automatically splitting complex tasks\n- **Fast Mode**: 2.5x speed improvement\n- **SWE-bench Verified score**: 80.8% (industry-leading)\n- **Pricing**: $30/$150 per million tokens\n\n**Claude Sonnet 4.6** (Released February 17, 2026)\n- Sonnet-level pricing with Opus-level coding capabilities\n- **Pricing**: $3/$15 per million tokens\n- Enhanced performance in coding, agentic tasks, computer use, and long-context reasoning\n- **SWE-bench Verified**: ~75%\n- Default model for free/Pro users\n\n**Claude Haiku 4.5**\n- Lightweight fast version for simple tasks\n- **Pricing**: $0.25 per million tokens\n\n---\n\n## **Claude Code 2.1 Major Update (January 7-9, 2026)**\n\nThis was described as the **largest single update in Claude Code history**, merging **1,096 code commits** and jumping from version 2.0.76 to 2.1.0 (with 2.1.1 as a quick hotfix).\n\n### **Key Features Added:**\n\n1. **Skills Hot Reload** - Skill files take effect immediately without restarting Claude Code\n2. **Shift+Enter for line breaks** - Works out-of-the-box without configuration\n3. **/teleport command** - Transfer sessions between devices (e.g., work computer to home computer)\n4. **Multi-language response configuration** - Configure model responses in specific languages (e.g., Japanese, Spanish, Simplified Chinese)\n5. **Tool permission wildcards** - Support wildcard matching for tool permissions\n6. **Agent behavior optimization** - Agents no longer terminate when tool use is refused; they attempt alternative solutions\n7. **Hooks support** - Add hooks directly in Agent and Skill frontmatter\n8. **Async sub-agents** - New asynchronous agent capabilities\n9. **Vim operation extensions**\n10. **MCP dynamic updates**\n\n### **Update Breakdown:**\n- **30+ new features**\n- **40+ bug fixes** (security vulnerabilities, Chinese input, terminal compatibility, etc.)\n- **10+ performance and experience optimizations**\n\n### **Installation Commands:**\n```bash\nnpm update -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code\n# or\nnpm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code@2.1.1\n```\n\n---\n\n## **Important Note**\n\n⚠️ **All of this information comes from third-party articles and blog posts** (primarily Chinese tech news sites). I could not find any official release notes, blog posts, or documentation from **anthropic.com** or **claude.ai** for February 2026 specifically.\n\nFor official information, I recommend:\n- Checking the official [Anthropic blog](https://www.anthropic.com/blog)\n- Visiting [Claude Code documentation](https://docs.anthropic.com)\n- Reviewing the [Claude Code GitHub repository](https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code) for official changelogs\n\nWould you like me to search for official documentation or GitHub repositories instead?\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
