ooks of content\n- **Agent Teams multi-agent collaboration** - multiple AI agents work in parallel, automatically splitting complex tasks\n- **Fast Mode** - 2.5x speed improvement\n- **SWE-bench Verified score**: 80.8% (industry-leading)\n- **Price**: $30/$150 per million tokens\n\n## **Claude Sonnet 4.6** (Released February 17, 2026)\n\nDubbed **\"the strongest Sonnet in history,\"** it was released just 12 days after Opus 4.6.\n\n### Key Features:\n- **Opus-level performance at Sonnet-level pricing** ($3/$15 per million tokens - 1/5th the cost of Opus)\n- **1 million token context window** (beta)\n- **SWE-bench Verified score**: ~75% to 79.6%\n- **Default model** for free/Pro users\n- Major upgrades in: coding, agent tasks, computer use, and long-context reasoning\n- **1633 Elo** in office task evaluations, surpassing Opus 4.6\n\n## **Claude Code Integration**\n\nAccording to the search results, **Claude Code early testing showed remarkable user preferences**:\n- ~70% of developers preferred Sonnet 4.6 over the previous Sonnet 4.5\n- 59% preferred Sonnet 4.6 over last year's Opus 4.5\n\n### Claude Code User Experience Improvements:\n- Better understanding of context before modifying code\n- Reduced unnecessary code repetition\n- Better integration of shared logic\n- More reliable and stable multi-step task execution\n- Less \"over-designing\" and \"laziness\"\n- Better instruction following\n- Fewer hallucinations and false success claims\n\n## Model Selection Recommendations\n\n**Use Sonnet 4.6 for:**\n- Daily programming/Claude Code tasks\n- Content creation/writing assistance\n- Computer automation tasks\n- Large-scale API calls\n- Most office and financial tasks\n\n**Use Opus 4.6 for:**\n- Deep scientific reasoning\n- Large-scale code refactoring\n- Multi-agent orchestration\n- Zero-error tolerance scenarios\n\nBoth models represent a significant leap forward in AI capabilities for 2026, with Sonnet 4.6 being particularly notable for achieving near-flagship performance at a fraction of the cost.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
