ent from the future (February 2026), which suggests these may be speculative or incorrect dates in the sources. However, I'll summarize the reactions as reported:\n\n### Key User Feedback Themes Reported:\n\n#### **Positive Reactions:**\n\n1. **Performance vs. Value**\n   - Users praised Sonnet 4.6 for delivering near-Opus level performance at Sonnet-level pricing\n   - One developer quoted: \"Claude Sonnet 4.6 以更低的成本实现了接近Opus的智能水平，这意义非凡，适用于预算有限的团队\" (Claude Sonnet 4.6 achieves near-Opus intelligence at lower cost - significant for budget-constrained teams)\n\n2. **100万 Token上下文窗口 (1M Token Context Window)**\n   - Multiple developers highlighted the 1 million token context window as a major feature\n   - User comment: \"100万个token？终于找到一个能读取我整个混乱代码库而不评判我的模型了\" (1 million tokens? Finally found a model that can read my entire messy codebase without judging it)\n\n3. **Programming Improvements**\n   - Anthropic's internal testing reportedly showed **70% of users preferred Sonnet 4.6 over Sonnet 4.5**\n   - **59% preferred it over the flagship Opus 4.5**\n   - Users noted: reduced \"laziness,\" better instruction following, fewer hallucinations, and more stable multi-step task execution\n\n4. **Computer Use Capabilities**\n   - OSWorld benchmark score improved from 14.9% (Oct 2024) to 72.5% (Feb 2026) - a **387% improvement in 16 months**\n   - Twitter user @CodeByPoonam highlighted the 72.5% OSWorld score and 79.6% SWE-bench score\n\n#### **Mixed/Critical Reactions:**\n\n1. **Unmet Expectations**\n   - Some developers expressed disappointment that Sonnet 4.6 didn't exceed expectations\n   - Comments like: \"We originally expected Sonnet 4.6 to outperform Opus 4.5 in programming, but results show it's just a Cowork upgrade\"\n   - Some remarked \"Sonnet 4.6 = Opus 4.5\"\n\n2. **Security Concerns**\n   - Developers raised concerns about Copilot Agent mode code security\n   - Worry about agents with production environment commit permissions posing supply chain risks\n\n3. **Competitor Comparisons**\n   - Some users noted Sonnet 4.6 didn't surpass GPT-5.2\n   - Questions raised about lack of comparison with Codex 5.3\n\n### Platform Integration Reactions:\n\n- **Immediate adoption** across platforms: Cursor, GitHub, Replit, Bolt all integrated Sonnet 4.6\n- **Stock market impact:** Software stocks reportedly declined following the release (Intuit -5%, Oracle -3%, Salesforce -2%, Adobe -1%)\n\n### Twitter/X Specific Reactions:\n\n- Multiple developers shared code generation examples and comparisons\n- Visual/SVG generation capabilities were showcased and compared favorably to competitors\n- Users demonstrated real-world applications including automated content generation workflows\n\n---\n\n**Important Note:** Please verify that the information you're seeking relates to actual events, as the search results reference February 2026 dates, which is in the future from the current date of July 2025. If you're looking for current information about Claude models, I'd be happy to search for more recent and accurate data.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
